  "prompt": "How do I import my Gmail contacts into Skype?",
  "response": "To import your Gmail contacts into Skype, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Export Contacts from Gmail:**\n   - Open Gmail and click on the \"Google apps\" icon (a grid icon) in the top right corner.\n   - Select \"Contacts\" from the dropdown menu.\n   - Once in Google Contacts, click on \"Export\" from the left sidebar.\n   - Choose the contacts you want to export or select \"All contacts.\"\n   - Select the export format as \"vCard (for iOS Contacts)\" or \"CSV (for Outlook)\" depending on what is supported by your Skype version.\n   - Click \"Export\" and save the file to your computer.\n\n2. **Import Contacts into Skype:**\n   - Open Skype and sign in with your account.\n   - In Skype, go to the \"Contacts\" section or the main menu.\n   - Look for an option like \"Import Contacts\" or \"Contacts\" > \"Import\"\n   - If there is an option to upload a file, choose the vCard or CSV file you exported from Gmail.\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the import process.\n\nNote: The exact steps might vary slightly depending on the version of Skype you are using. Also, some features might not be available if you are using Skype for Web or less common platform versions.\n\nIf Skype's built-in import functionality does not support direct import from a file, you may have to add contacts manually or explore third-party solutions that facilitate syncing contacts between services.",
